COVID-19 Vaccination Intention and Migration in Germany: The Role of Socio-Cultural Factors

Online Appendix

xxx

2021-11-11

Operationalization

The following gives an overview of the variables used in the article.

Vaccination intention

Instructions

None

Items

Abbr. Wording
vaxx How would you decide, if next week you had the possibility to get vaccinated against COVID-19?
[Wie würden Sie entscheiden, wenn Sie nächste Woche die Möglichkeit hätten, sich gegen COVID−19 impfen zu lassen?]

Responses

The response scale for the item was a seven-point rating scale with end points labelled: 1 “would not vaccinate at all” and 7 “would vaccinate definetly” [1 “auf keinen Fall impfen” and 7 “auf jeden Fall impfen”].

Fear of Coronavirus

Instructions

Please tell us to what extent the following statements concerning the Coronavirus apply to you.

[Bitte geben Sie an, wie sehr die folgenden Aussagen in Bezug auf das Coronavirus zutreffen.]

Items

Abbr. Wording
fear_infect I am afraid of getting infected by the Coronavirus.
[Ich fürchte mich davor, mit Corona infiziert zu werden.]
fear_contr I am afraid of infecting my family and friends with the virus.
[Ich fürchte mich davor, Angehörige und Freunde mit dem Virus anzustecken.]

Responses

The response scale for each item was a seven-point rating scale with end points labelled: 1 “do not agree at all” und 7 “agree fully”.

Health consciousness

Instructions

To what extent do you agree with the following statements?

[Inwiefern stimmen Sie den folgenden Aussagen zu?]

Items

Abbr. Wording
h_worry I am worried about my health.
[Ich mache mir Sorgen um die eigene Gesundheit.]
h_imp I am very shocked when there are reports about serious diseases in the media.
[Wenn in den Medien über schwere Krankheiten berichtet wird, bin ich immer ganz erschüttert.]
media_di There is nothing more important in life than thinking about your health .
[Es gibt im Leben gar nichts Wichtigeres, als an die Gesundheit zu denken.]

Responses

The response scale for each item was a seven-point rating scale with end points labelled: 1 “do not agree at all” und 7 “agree fully”.

Notes

All three items are used as indicators of the latent factor health consciousness (h_cons)

Political Trust

Instructions

I am going to name a variety of public institutions and organisations. Please tell me about every institution or organisation the degree of trust you have towards it. To what degree do you trust…

[Ich nenne Ihnen jetzt eine Reihe von öffentlichen Einrichtungen und Organisationen. Sagen Sie mir bitte bei jeder Einrichtung oder Organisation, wie groß das Vertrauen ist, das Sie ihr entgegenbringen. Wie hoch ist ihr Vertrauen gegenüber…]

Items

Abbr. Wording
otrust_gov the federal government
[der Bundesregierung]
otrust_hth the health agency
[dem Gesundheitsamt]
otrust_med the media
[den Medien]
otrust_pol the police
[der Polizei]
otrust_parl the parliament
[dem Bundestag]

Responses

The response scale for each item was a seven-point rating scale with end points labelled: 1 “no trust at all” und 7 “a lot of trust”. [1 “überhaupt kein Vertrauen” and 7 “sehr großes Vertrauen”].

Notes

Four of the five items are used as indicators of the latent factor political trust (pol_trust)

Religiosity

Instructions

None

Items

Abbr. Wording
vaxx Would you say about yourself that you are rather religious or rather unreligous? I am…
[Würden Sie von sich sagen, dass Sie eher religiös oder eher nicht religiös sind? Ich bin..]

Responses

The response scale for the item was a seven-point rating scale with end points labelled: 1 “not religious at all” and 7 “very religious” [1 “gar nicht religiös” and 7 “sehr religiös”].

Media consumption

Instructions

Now, lets talk about your life in Germany. To what degree apply the following statements? [Nun geht es um Ihr Leben in Deutschland. Inwiefern treffen folgende Aussagen für Sie zu?]

Items

Abbr. Wording
media_cor I use media from my/ my parents’ country of origin (tv, radio, newspaper, magazines etc.)
[Ich benutze Medien aus meinem Herkunftsland bzw. aus dem Herkunftsland meiner Eltern (TV, Radio, Zeitung, Zeitschriften etc.)]
media_ger I use German media (tv, radio, newspaper, magazines etc.)
[Ich benutze deutsche Medien (TV, Radio, Zeitung, Zeitschriften etc.)]

Responses

The response scale for each item was a seven-point rating scale with end points labelled: 1 “does not apply at all” und 7 “applies fully” [1 “trifft überhaupt nicht zu” and 7 “trifft voll und ganz zu”].

Years Since Migration

Instructions

Since when do you live in Germany (also former GDR) If you came from another country than Germany, please state when you moved to Germany for the first time, even if you lived somewhere else. [Seit wann leben Sie in Deutschland (auch DDR)? Wenn Sie aus einem anderen Land als Deutschland herkommen, bitte geben Sie an wann Sie das erste Mal nach Deutschland gezogen sind, auch wenn Sie mal woanders gelebt haben.]

Items

Abbr. Wording
ysm Since…
[Seit…]

Responses

The response scale for the item was a dropdown selection ranging from “before 1950” to “2020”

Notes

This item was recoded to get a numeric variable that counts the years since migration until 2021.

Demographic Covariates

Items

Abbr. Variable
educ Educational Attainment [1=upper secondary and higher, 0=lower secondary and lower]
sex Gender [1=male, 0=female]
age Age [in years]
inc Personal net monthly income [1=less than 500, 9=more than 4000]

Notes

The “still going to school” category was recoded as missing value. The third “diverse” category for gender only yielded n=3 respondents, who were then recoded as missing values. Age was computed from the birth year question by subtracting birth year from the survey year 2021. Birth year was inquired in the survey via dropdown selection.

Models

The following contains the full code and summary outputs of the models featured in the article.

Two datasets are created, the all respondents dataset (n=1027) and the migrants only dataset (n=389)

model01 <- '
  # Identify latent factors
  #identify latent factors
  h_cons =~ h_worry  + media_di + h_imp
  pol_trust =~ otrust_gov + otrust_hth + otrust_med + otrust_pol #+ otrust_parl 
  
  #error correlations
  otrust_med ~~ otrust_pol
  otrust_gov ~~ otrust_hth
  
'
fit_m01 <- sem(model01, df1, meanstructure = TRUE, missing = "fiml")
df1_pr <- as.data.frame(lavPredict(fit_m01, newdata=df1, type= "lv", method="ML", label=T, append.data = T))

Empirical model 1, all respondents

Empirical model 1 of vaccination intention for all respondents according the hypothesized structure as suggested in Fig.1 in the article (without dashed lines).

Click ‘Code’ to see syntax

model1 <- '
#measurement model
h_cons =~ h_worry  + media_di + h_imp
pol_trust =~ otrust_gov + otrust_hth + otrust_med + otrust_pol #+ otrust_parl 

#Covariances
educ ~~ sex + mig + age + inc
sex ~~ mig + age + inc 
mig ~~ age + inc 
age ~~ inc 

pol_trust ~~ h_cons + vaxx

#Error Correlations
fear_infect ~~ fear_contr
h_worry ~~ fear_infect 
otrust_med ~~ otrust_pol
otrust_gov ~~  otrust_hth

#regressions
vaxx ~ a1*fear_infect + b1*fear_contr + e1*educ + f1*sex + g1*inc + h1*age
fear_infect ~ a2*pol_trust  + c2*h_cons + d2*educ + e2*sex + f2*inc + g2*age  
fear_contr ~  a3*pol_trust  + c3*h_cons + d3*educ + e3*sex + f3*inc + g3*age 
pol_trust ~  a4*mig + b4*rel + c4*educ + d4*sex + e4*inc + f4*age
h_cons ~ a6*mig + b6*rel + c6*educ + d6*sex + e6*inc + f6*age
rel ~ a7*mig + c7*educ + d7*sex + e7*inc + f7*age

#total effect of migration

m1:= a7*b6*c2*a1 #mig-rel-hcon-inf-vaxx 
m2:= a7*b6*c3*b1 #mig-rel-hcon-contr-vaxx 
m3:= a7*b4*a2*a1 #mig-rel-trust-inf-vaxx 
m4:= a7*b4*a3*b1 #mig-rel-trust-contr-vaxx 

totmig:= m1+m2+m3+m4

'

fit_m1 <- sem(model1, df1, meanstructure=T, missing="fiml")
Click here for output

Empirical model 1+, all respondents with additional paths

Empirical model 1+ of vaccination intention for all respondents as in Fig.1 in the article (with dashed lines).

Click ‘Code’ to see syntax

model2 <- '
#measurement model
h_cons =~ h_worry  + media_di + h_imp
pol_trust =~ otrust_gov + otrust_hth + otrust_med + otrust_pol #+ otrust_parl 

#Covariances
educ ~~ sex + mig + age + inc
sex ~~ mig + age + inc 
mig ~~ age + inc 
age ~~ inc 

h_cons ~~ pol_trust + vaxx

#Error Correlations
fear_infect ~~ fear_contr
h_worry ~~ fear_infect 

otrust_med ~~ otrust_pol
otrust_gov ~~  otrust_hth

#regressions
vaxx ~ a1*fear_infect + b1*fear_contr  + i1*mig + x1*rel + e1*educ + f1*sex + g1*inc + h1*age + k1*pol_trust 
fear_infect ~ a2*pol_trust  + c2*h_cons + d2*educ + e2*sex + f2*inc + g2*age  
fear_contr ~  a3*pol_trust  + c3*h_cons + d3*educ + e3*sex + f3*inc + g3*age + x3*rel
pol_trust ~  a4*mig + b4*rel + c4*educ + d4*sex + e4*inc + f4*age
h_cons ~ a6*mig + b6*rel + c6*educ + d6*sex + e6*inc + f6*age
rel ~ a7*mig + c7*educ + d7*sex + e7*inc + f7*age

#total effect of migration

m1:= a7*b6*c2*a1 #mig-rel-hcon-inf-vaxx 
m2:= a7*b6*c3*b1 #mig-rel-hcon-contr-vaxx 
m3:= a7*b4*a2*a1 #mig-rel-trust-inf-vaxx 
m4:= a7*b4*a3*b1 #mig-rel-trust-contr-vaxx 

m5:= a7*b4*k1    #mig-rel-trust-vaxx 
m6:= a7*x3*b1    #mig-rel-contr-vaxx
m7:= a7*x1    #mig-rel-vaxx

totmig:= m1+m2+m3+m4+m5+m6+m7+i1

'

fit_m2 <- sem(model2, df1, meanstructure=T, missing="fiml")

Empirical model 2, migrants only

Empirical model 2 of vaccination intention for migrants only, according the hypothesized structure as suggested in Fig.1 in the article (without dashed lines).

Click ‘Code’ to see syntax

model_m1 <- '
  #measurement model
  h_cons =~ h_worry  + media_di + h_imp 
  pol_trust =~ otrust_gov + otrust_hth + otrust_med +  otrust_pol #+ otrust_parl 

  #Covariances
  educ ~~ age + sex + inc + ysm  + euro
  age ~~ sex + inc + ysm  + euro 
  sex ~~ inc + ysm  + euro 
  inc ~~ ysm  + euro 
  ysm ~~ euro 

  
pol_trust ~~ h_cons + vaxx
  
#Error Correlations
fear_infect ~~ fear_contr  
h_worry ~~ fear_infect 
media_cor ~~ media_ger

otrust_med ~~ otrust_pol
otrust_gov ~~  otrust_hth

#regressions
vaxx ~ a1*fear_infect + b1*fear_contr  + e1*educ + f1*sex + g1*inc + h1*age 
fear_infect ~ a2*pol_trust  + d2*h_cons +  j2*educ + k2*sex + l2*inc + m2*age 
fear_contr ~  a3*pol_trust + d3*h_cons + j3*educ + k3*sex + l3*inc + m3*age 
pol_trust ~  a4*media_cor + b4*media_ger  + x4*ysm + h4*euro + c4*rel + d4*educ + e4*sex + f4*inc + g4*age
h_cons ~ a6*media_cor + b6*media_ger + x6*ysm  + d6*euro + e6*rel + f6*educ + g6*sex + h6*inc + i6*age
media_cor ~ a7*ysm + b7*euro + c7*educ + d7*sex + e7*inc + f7*age 
media_ger ~ a8*ysm + b8*euro + c8*educ + d8*sex + e8*inc + f8*age 
rel ~ a9*ysm + b9*euro + c9*educ + d9*sex + e9*inc + f9*age 
'

fit_m1 <- sem(model_m1, df_m, meanstructure=T, missing="fiml")

Empirical model 2+, migrants only with additional paths

Empirical model 2+ of vaccination intention for migrants only as in Fig.1 in the article (with dashed lines).

Click ‘Code’ to see syntax

model_m2 <- '
  #measurement model
  h_cons =~ h_worry  + media_di + h_imp 
  pol_trust =~ otrust_gov + otrust_hth + otrust_med +  otrust_pol #+ otrust_parl 

  #Covariances
  educ ~~ age + sex + inc + ysm  + euro
  age ~~ sex + inc + ysm  + euro 
  sex ~~ inc + ysm  + euro 
  inc ~~ ysm  + euro 
  ysm ~~ euro 

pol_trust ~~ h_cons + vaxx
  
#Error Correlations
fear_infect ~~ fear_contr  
h_worry ~~ fear_infect 
media_cor ~~ media_ger

otrust_med ~~ otrust_pol
otrust_gov ~~  otrust_hth


#regressions

vaxx ~ a1*fear_infect + b1*fear_contr  + e1*educ + f1*sex + g1*inc + h1*age + x1*euro + y1*rel + q1*media_ger
fear_infect ~ a2*pol_trust  + d2*h_cons +  j2*educ + k2*sex + l2*inc + m2*age + n2*euro
fear_contr ~  a3*pol_trust + d3*h_cons + j3*educ + k3*sex + l3*inc + m3*age 
pol_trust ~  a4*media_cor + b4*media_ger  + x4*ysm + h4*euro + c4*rel + d4*educ + e4*sex + f4*inc + g4*age
h_cons ~ a6*media_cor + b6*media_ger + x6*ysm  + d6*euro + e6*rel + f6*educ + g6*sex + h6*inc + i6*age
media_cor ~ a7*ysm + b7*euro + c7*educ + d7*sex + e7*inc + f7*age 
media_ger ~ a8*ysm + b8*euro + c8*educ + d8*sex + e8*inc + f8*age 
rel ~ a9*ysm + b9*euro + c9*educ + d9*sex + e9*inc + f9*age 
'


fit_m2 <- sem(model_m2, df_m, meanstructure=T, missing="fiml")
